    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, n. <citedRange>56</citedRange>, without illustration</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>010430</citedRange></bibl>.</p>           
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ώι"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F"><unclear>ὼι</unclear></seg></name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀριστ_" type="patronymic"><seg part="I">Ἀριστ</seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName></persName>
                    </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
               <p>
                   <app loc="1"><rdg resp="#robinson1913"><orig>ιιαριστ</orig></rdg></app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ô fille d'Arist<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>o daughter of Arist<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ò figlia di Arist<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>From the photograph, it is possible to see a difference between both strokes at the beginning; the first one being curved, belonged to an omega,
                    while the second one is straight. We thus get the ending of a feminine name in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-ώι</foreign>. There are no distinctive features in this small fragment and 
                nothing is known about its findspot, so it is impossible to know which type of inscription contained this woman's name.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
